<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4447] Allow hbase.version to be passed in as command-line argument</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4447</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the build always produces the jars and tarball according to the version baked into the POM.&lt;br/&gt;
When we modify this to allow the version to be passed in as a command-line argument, it can still default to the same behavior, yet give the flexibility for an internal build to tag on own version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12523652">HBASE-4447</key>
            <summary>Allow hbase.version to be passed in as command-line argument</summary>
